<%- include('partials/header') %>

<div class="fade-in">
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <div class="relative bg-gradient-to-b from-gray-900 to-black py-24">
    <div
      class="absolute inset-0 bg-[url('/images/business-bg.jpg')] bg-cover bg-center opacity-20"
    ></div>
    <div class="relative container mx-auto px-6">
      <h1 class="text-6xl font-bold chrome-text mb-6 tracking-tight">
        DECPTION
      </h1>
      <p class="text-2xl text-gray-300 max-w-2xl">Streetwear with a Strategy</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Main Content -->
  <div class="container mx-auto px-6 py-16">
    <!-- Metrics Section -->
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto mb-16">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
        <!-- Metric 1 -->
        <div class="bg-gray-900 p-8 rounded-lg border border-gray-800">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold chrome-text mb-4">Revenue Growth</h3>
          <p class="text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-2">$5K+</p>
          <p class="text-gray-400">Initial Revenue</p>
        </div>
        <!-- Metric 2 -->
        <div class="bg-gray-900 p-8 rounded-lg border border-gray-800">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold chrome-text mb-4">Marketing ROI</h3>
          <p class="text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-2">Data-Driven</p>
          <p class="text-gray-400">Performance Based</p>
        </div>
        <!-- Metric 3 -->
        <div class="bg-gray-900 p-8 rounded-lg border border-gray-800">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold chrome-text mb-4">Growth Strategy</h3>
          <p class="text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-2">A/B</p>
          <p class="text-gray-400">Testing Focus</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Brand Story Section -->
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto mb-16">
      <div class="bg-gray-900 p-8 rounded-lg border border-gray-800">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold chrome-text mb-8">THE STORY</h2>
        <div class="space-y-8 text-gray-300 text-lg leading-relaxed">
          <p>
            Deception is more than just a clothing brand — it's a movement built
            on vision, authenticity, and data-driven marketing. Co-founded with
            my best friend, who is also an influencer, we launched Deception to
            fill a gap in the streetwear space with a focus on clean aesthetics,
            bold identity, and community connection. From day one, we committed
            not only to designing high-quality pieces but to building a brand
            that resonates through both visual culture and performance-based
            strategy.
          </p>

          <p>
            Our most effective growth strategy has been influencer marketing. By
            leveraging my co-founder's social presence and our personal network
            of creators, we were able to generate authentic engagement and
            expand Deception's reach rapidly. This organic momentum gave us the
            launchpad to test Facebook Ads and scale our campaigns while
            maintaining the voice and vision of the brand. Each post, reel, or
            story was more than content — it was a conversion opportunity that
            fit seamlessly into our customers' lifestyles.
          </p>

          <p>
            Using Facebook Ads, we ran A/B tests across different creatives,
            copy variations, and audience segments. I personally tracked metrics
            like click-through rate (CTR), cost-per-click (CPC), return on ad
            spend (ROAS), and conversion rate. Every campaign became a feedback
            loop — we'd measure performance, optimize what worked, and drop what
            didn't. This approach allowed us to sharpen our targeting, refine
            our messaging, and steadily increase profitability.
          </p>

          <p>
            Through this analytical process, we generated over $5,000 in
            revenue, reinvesting most of our profits back into ad spend,
            improved visuals, and supply chain upgrades. Every dollar earned
            wasn't just income — it was fuel for better strategy and smarter
            growth. I built dashboards, monitored data daily, and made
            performance-based decisions that directly influenced our product
            drops and ad campaigns.
          </p>

          <p>
            Building Deception while studying full-time has been a masterclass
            in real-world business execution. It's taught me how to manage
            pressure, stay focused, and lead with both creativity and
            accountability. I've gained firsthand experience in customer
            experience, product iteration, and brand storytelling — all while
            tracking analytics and learning how to scale efficiently on limited
            resources.
          </p>

          <p>
            As Deception grows, my goal is to turn it into a brand that stands
            at the intersection of culture and conversion. Every design has
            meaning, every ad has intent, and every customer interaction is an
            opportunity to build loyalty. This business isn't just a side
            project — it's where I apply the skills I'm learning in computer
            programming, data analytics, and digital marketing every single day.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Gallery Section -->
